1
00:00:41,855 --> 00:00:43,450
Good morning.

2
00:00:43,450 --> 00:00:44,670
Good morning.

3
00:00:45,960 --> 00:00:47,760
Nice weather today, huh?

4
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:49,990
Yeah, it is.

5
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:03,974
[Episode 2]

6
00:02:03,974 --> 00:02:05,614
The second is...

7
00:02:07,169 --> 00:02:11,784
setting off fireworks.
[One week ago]

8
00:02:11,784 --> 00:02:13,494
Fireworks?

9
00:02:15,010 --> 00:02:18,030
It's weird coming
from someone who can't see, right?

10
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:20,235
No, um...

11
00:02:20,235 --> 00:02:22,755
But I love them.

12
00:02:24,860 --> 00:02:26,180
Why?

13
00:02:28,328 --> 00:02:30,973
Since I lost my sight,

14
00:02:30,973 --> 00:02:34,673
I was always looking down,
afraid of tripping.

15
00:02:35,820 --> 00:02:37,460
But one day,

16
00:02:38,235 --> 00:02:43,510
when I heard the boom of fireworks,

17
00:02:43,510 --> 00:02:47,530
I looked up at the sky.

18
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:53,930
In that moment when the fireworks go off,

19
00:02:53,930 --> 00:02:55,970
everyone looks up.

20
00:02:57,010 --> 00:02:59,960
I think that's really beautiful.

21
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:04,030
That's why.

22
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:07,120
Looking up, huh?

23
00:03:09,785 --> 00:03:11,830
That's nice.

24
00:03:11,830 --> 00:03:13,390
Isn't it?

25
00:03:14,440 --> 00:03:15,480
Ah...

26
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,280
Yeah.

27
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,520
If it's okay,

28
00:03:22,940 --> 00:03:26,320
would you like to do it together?

29
00:03:27,105 --> 00:03:28,290
Huh?

30
00:03:28,290 --> 00:03:31,055
Dude, that's totally a date!

31
00:03:31,055 --> 00:03:33,275
I'm just helping her shop.

32
00:03:34,173 --> 00:03:38,480
There's a fireworks shop
in Asakusa, apparently.

33
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:41,230
And what are you reading?

34
00:03:41,230 --> 00:03:43,465
I borrowed it from the library.

35
00:03:43,465 --> 00:03:45,915
A manual for giving assistance?

36
00:03:47,019 --> 00:03:51,090
I never thought an aloof guy like you
would go this far.

37
00:03:51,090 --> 00:03:53,640
It's not like that.

38
00:03:56,040 --> 00:04:01,955
I just wanted to try to connect
with people a little more, that's all.

39
00:04:03,570 --> 00:04:07,125
How did Koharu lose her sight?

40
00:04:07,125 --> 00:04:08,180
Not sure.

41
00:04:08,180 --> 00:04:09,990
Didn't ask?

42
00:04:09,990 --> 00:04:13,020
If I ask, I might hurt her feelings.

43
00:04:15,175 --> 00:04:19,830
Connecting with someone
means getting to know them, right?

44
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:24,490
You need to learn more about her
to support her properly.

45
00:04:32,143 --> 00:04:33,323
I'm sleeping now.

46
00:04:37,970 --> 00:04:39,310
Good night.

47
00:04:56,350 --> 00:04:58,810
<i>Ushio was right.</i>

48
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:04,460
<i>I still don't know anything about Koharu.</i>

49
00:05:12,780 --> 00:05:14,570
Sorry for the wait.

50
00:05:15,385 --> 00:05:18,270
I just got here, too.

51
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:19,340
Okay.

52
00:05:20,580 --> 00:05:22,960
Well then, shall we go?

53
00:05:23,995 --> 00:05:26,380
Oh, um...

54
00:05:26,380 --> 00:05:28,466
Go straight, 12 o'clock.

55
00:05:28,466 --> 00:05:29,606
Got it.

56
00:05:35,836 --> 00:05:39,731
Let me know
if there are any steps or obstacles.

57
00:05:39,731 --> 00:05:40,991
Okay.

58
00:05:52,230 --> 00:05:55,349
Is this Asakusa?

59
00:05:55,349 --> 00:05:57,859
Does it smell like Asakusa to you?

60
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:01,290
I can't really tell.

61
00:06:03,650 --> 00:06:06,640
We still have to walk a bit
to the fireworks shop.

62
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,180
Watch out!

63
00:06:11,260 --> 00:06:12,410
Are you okay?

64
00:06:14,575 --> 00:06:17,000
Thank you...

65
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,085
I completely let my guard down.

66
00:06:20,085 --> 00:06:22,375
Oh, um...

67
00:06:24,010 --> 00:06:27,150
We'll be walking through a crowd for a while.

68
00:06:28,415 --> 00:06:30,826
So I'll stay alert.

69
00:06:30,826 --> 00:06:32,276
No, I mean...

70
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,790
Do you want to...

71
00:06:35,565 --> 00:06:37,310
grab on to me?

72
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:38,400
Huh?

73
00:06:39,306 --> 00:06:40,506
My arm.

74
00:06:41,270 --> 00:06:43,040
If it's fine with you.

75
00:06:58,030 --> 00:06:59,930
Yes, please.

76
00:07:01,430 --> 00:07:02,430
Okay.

77
00:07:10,875 --> 00:07:14,130
I'll start walking then.

78
00:07:14,130 --> 00:07:15,370
Okay.

79
00:07:34,918 --> 00:07:37,093
Shall we go this way?

80
00:07:37,093 --> 00:07:38,243
Okay.

81
00:07:44,860 --> 00:07:46,660
I think you can let go now.

82
00:07:47,805 --> 00:07:49,690
- Okay.
- Good.

83
00:07:51,460 --> 00:07:54,700
Asakusa on a Sunday is amazing, isn't it?

84
00:07:55,335 --> 00:07:58,070
We still have a bit of a walk.

85
00:07:58,070 --> 00:07:59,080
Okay.

86
00:08:01,470 --> 00:08:04,935
There's a café over there.
Want to take a break?

87
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:07,990
Sure.

88
00:08:11,155 --> 00:08:13,390
Welcome!

89
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:15,015
There's a door.

90
00:08:15,015 --> 00:08:16,496
Thank you.

91
00:08:20,925 --> 00:08:23,620
Sorry, table for two.

92
00:08:23,620 --> 00:08:25,160
Huh?

93
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,880
Yuuko?

94
00:08:26,880 --> 00:08:28,845
Kakeru.

95
00:08:28,845 --> 00:08:31,295
And Koharu?

96
00:08:32,495 --> 00:08:35,650
Hey, you're buying fireworks together?

97
00:08:35,650 --> 00:08:38,210
When did you two get so close?

98
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:40,130
It's not like that.

99
00:08:40,130 --> 00:08:41,665
Sure, sure.

100
00:08:41,665 --> 00:08:43,845
Well, take your time.

101
00:08:46,705 --> 00:08:48,980
That was unexpected, huh?

102
00:08:48,980 --> 00:08:50,140
Yeah.

103
00:08:52,015 --> 00:08:54,730
You're really not eating anything?

104
00:08:54,730 --> 00:08:56,780
I'm not hungry.

105
00:08:57,690 --> 00:08:59,030
I see.

106
00:09:00,415 --> 00:09:03,240
It's been so long
since I last came out without family,

107
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:06,040
so I'm enjoying this very much.

108
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,830
But...

109
00:09:14,055 --> 00:09:16,290
I'm not doing well at all, am I?

110
00:09:16,290 --> 00:09:19,950
I feel like I'm not helping out at all.

111
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:26,600
I've been thinking
about what you need, but...

112
00:09:28,876 --> 00:09:32,026
I don't even know much about you yet.

113
00:09:32,777 --> 00:09:34,417
For example...

114
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:38,440
what do you want to know about me?

115
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:41,560
Um...

116
00:09:47,211 --> 00:09:52,800
Like, what can I do to help you out
or make you happy?

117
00:09:54,586 --> 00:09:57,536
Or even before any of that...

118
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:09,170
how did you lose your sight, for example?

119
00:10:09,170 --> 00:10:11,985
Oh, only if you're comfortable telling me.

120
00:10:11,985 --> 00:10:13,635
Do you want to hear?

121
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,090
Is that okay?

122
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:20,680
Yes.

123
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,700
They found cancer in both of my eyes.

124
00:10:29,880 --> 00:10:32,200
I was a high school freshman.

125
00:10:33,755 --> 00:10:36,300
It's called intraocular lymphoma,

126
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:39,980
a disease that could cause
blindness or metastasis.

127
00:10:42,070 --> 00:10:45,486
I started chemotherapy right away.

128
00:10:45,486 --> 00:10:49,376
But my vision kept getting worse.

129
00:10:50,716 --> 00:10:55,026
They completely cured my cancer,
but I became completely blind.

130
00:10:58,315 --> 00:11:02,180
After that, I waited to regain my strength,

131
00:11:02,180 --> 00:11:05,733
learned Braille, studied,

132
00:11:05,733 --> 00:11:09,193
and entered college a year late.

133
00:11:12,395 --> 00:11:16,940
But now that I've dumped this on you,

134
00:11:16,940 --> 00:11:20,260
you probably feel awkward
around me now, right?

135
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:27,460
Thank you for listening to all of this.

136
00:11:35,530 --> 00:11:36,940
I see.

137
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:46,060
But wait.

138
00:11:47,296 --> 00:11:51,255
If you joined a year late,

139
00:11:51,255 --> 00:11:53,510
are we the same age?

140
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:54,275
Huh?

141
00:11:54,275 --> 00:11:58,134
Well, if that's true,
you should speak casually to me.

142
00:11:58,134 --> 00:12:00,370
Like with my name.

143
00:12:00,370 --> 00:12:04,860
It's okay to address me casually.

144
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,480
Just call my name.

145
00:12:12,645 --> 00:12:14,680
Huh?

146
00:12:14,680 --> 00:12:16,110
Sorry.

147
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:19,920
You're right.

148
00:12:22,827 --> 00:12:23,997
Yeah.

149
00:12:31,465 --> 00:12:33,650
Watch your step.

150
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:35,543
Thanks.

151
00:12:35,543 --> 00:12:36,993
Two more steps.

152
00:12:40,555 --> 00:12:43,230
Are you okay?
Is Kakeru guiding you properly?

153
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:45,315
Sorry for the wait.

154
00:12:45,315 --> 00:12:48,045
He's super reliable.

155
00:12:49,935 --> 00:12:52,510
All right, let's go.

156
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:53,725
Okay.

157
00:12:53,725 --> 00:12:55,095
Be careful.

158
00:12:56,790 --> 00:12:58,130
This way.

159
00:13:00,425 --> 00:13:01,740
Koharu.

160
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:03,730
Oh, okay.

161
00:13:14,660 --> 00:13:16,120
Take care.

162
00:13:22,670 --> 00:13:24,970
Wow...

163
00:13:26,295 --> 00:13:29,350
This is incredible.

164
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:32,170
The smell of gunpowder.

165
00:13:32,170 --> 00:13:34,780
It's like the night of a summer festival.

166
00:13:35,645 --> 00:13:37,226
Welcome.

167
00:13:37,226 --> 00:13:38,816
Looking for something?

168
00:13:39,815 --> 00:13:41,560
We want to launch fireworks.

169
00:13:41,560 --> 00:13:45,330
Oh, the shelves back there have some stuff.

170
00:13:47,385 --> 00:13:50,157
Hey, sir. Come here.

171
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,490
Should I explain the fireworks to you?

172
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:59,620
No, we'll both listen.

173
00:14:00,890 --> 00:14:02,840
We're shopping together.

174
00:14:03,525 --> 00:14:05,260
Got it. Okay.

175
00:14:05,260 --> 00:14:07,180
Come with me.

176
00:14:07,180 --> 00:14:09,615
Careful, miss. It's tight over there.

177
00:14:09,615 --> 00:14:10,745
Okay.

178
00:14:14,445 --> 00:14:18,180
This one has purple stars
spreading like a peony flower.

179
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:21,230
And this dragon one has a loud sound.

180
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:23,040
It's super intense.

181
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:26,195
Oh, intensity! You need something intense!

182
00:14:26,195 --> 00:14:27,615
Hold on.

183
00:14:29,790 --> 00:14:31,910
Some sound would be nice.

184
00:14:32,830 --> 00:14:34,040
Yes.

185
00:14:35,790 --> 00:14:38,970
Since we're here,
should we go for something flashy?

186
00:14:40,940 --> 00:14:42,130
Okay.

187
00:14:45,675 --> 00:14:48,660
Mission accomplished, yes?

188
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:49,860
Oh...

189
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:52,240
Hm?

190
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:55,170
We did it.

191
00:14:57,272 --> 00:15:00,152
It's okay, you can speak politely
if you want.

192
00:15:00,940 --> 00:15:02,310
Right.

193
00:15:03,275 --> 00:15:05,270
I'll work on it slowly.

194
00:15:05,270 --> 00:15:06,280
Yeah.

195
00:15:07,635 --> 00:15:10,940
Oh. I see the bus stop.

196
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:15,490
Today was fun.

197
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:16,490
Yeah.

198
00:15:17,620 --> 00:15:19,430
It went by so fast.

199
00:15:22,695 --> 00:15:24,590
Anything else?

200
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,590
Huh?

201
00:15:26,666 --> 00:15:28,996
On the list of things you want to do.

202
00:15:29,860 --> 00:15:31,370
Ah...

203
00:15:32,020 --> 00:15:34,590
It's still a secret.

204
00:15:36,010 --> 00:15:37,440
I see.

205
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:41,940
But there's so much
I haven't experienced yet.

206
00:15:41,940 --> 00:15:43,900
I want to try them all.

207
00:15:51,930 --> 00:15:53,480
What is it?

208
00:15:54,460 --> 00:15:56,400
A commuter boat?

209
00:15:57,248 --> 00:16:00,040
I guess it passes through here.

210
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:02,120
A commuter boat?

211
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:13,360
The breeze feels so nice.

212
00:16:15,145 --> 00:16:17,880
It feels like riding a bike.

213
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:19,680
What's that supposed to mean?

214
00:16:20,860 --> 00:16:23,220
That was the last boat of the day.

215
00:16:24,686 --> 00:16:26,786
Just our luck, huh?

216
00:16:27,695 --> 00:16:30,070
Yes.

217
00:16:30,070 --> 00:16:33,990
But thanks to that,
we got to come to such a nice place.

218
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:41,130
Kakeru.

219
00:16:42,010 --> 00:16:46,380
Can you tell me about the scenery...

220
00:16:47,090 --> 00:16:48,750
and the things you see?

221
00:16:53,556 --> 00:16:57,536
I see the Skytree to the left.

222
00:17:00,150 --> 00:17:07,550
The water in the river
is sparkling from the sun's reflection.

223
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:10,420
The river...

224
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:18,370
It smells nice.

225
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:21,525
This river used to be
really polluted long ago.

226
00:17:21,525 --> 00:17:23,915
Why would you tell me that?

227
00:17:25,890 --> 00:17:28,000
That was back then.

228
00:17:31,936 --> 00:17:33,266
Now...

229
00:17:45,076 --> 00:17:46,706
it's not bad.

230
00:17:52,867 --> 00:17:55,931
[Seimei University Dorms]

231
00:17:57,345 --> 00:17:59,280
Well then, let's hear it.

232
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,810
Today's heroic tale.

233
00:18:01,810 --> 00:18:02,725
Here.

234
00:18:02,725 --> 00:18:04,910
Why are you here, too?

235
00:18:04,910 --> 00:18:07,255
Tonight's gonna be a long one!

236
00:18:07,255 --> 00:18:08,725
Take off your shoes!

237
00:18:25,225 --> 00:18:27,170
It took so long...

238
00:18:27,170 --> 00:18:31,080
It took so long
to finally start looking forward.

239
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:35,324
It could still just be
a temporary abnormal value.

240
00:18:35,324 --> 00:18:41,594
But if further testing shows
the same result...

241
00:18:45,025 --> 00:18:47,420
that means it's back, right?

242
00:18:47,420 --> 00:18:51,245
Even so, many people
still reach full recovery.

243
00:18:51,245 --> 00:18:55,365
Please don't give up.

244
00:19:00,224 --> 00:19:02,325
- Koharu.
- Yeah?

245
00:19:02,325 --> 00:19:03,605
Your right cheek.

246
00:19:06,230 --> 00:19:07,640
Thanks.

247
00:19:08,497 --> 00:19:10,427
Didn't you eat lunch?

248
00:19:11,775 --> 00:19:13,420
Nope.

249
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:15,800
Didn't want to get your mouth messy?

250
00:19:17,955 --> 00:19:19,720
It's etiquette.

251
00:19:19,720 --> 00:19:23,250
But you went out to eat
with Yuuko before, right?

252
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,100
That was...

253
00:19:28,896 --> 00:19:31,776
You didn't want this person seeing you eat?

254
00:19:36,540 --> 00:19:39,050
How was it?

255
00:19:42,035 --> 00:19:45,170
I had a lot of fun.

256
00:19:45,170 --> 00:19:46,380
Really?

257
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:53,470
I told him why I lost my sight.

258
00:19:54,205 --> 00:19:56,000
I see.

259
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,445
And then?

260
00:19:57,445 --> 00:20:00,815
"You've been through a lot.
You did a great job..."

261
00:20:01,580 --> 00:20:04,020
That's what I was expecting.

262
00:20:05,038 --> 00:20:09,340
I didn't want to be looked at with sympathy.

263
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:10,680
Yeah.

264
00:20:12,755 --> 00:20:18,310
But then he said,
"Oh, are we the same age?"

265
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:20,840
"Then you should speak casually to me."

266
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,360
I see.

267
00:20:25,730 --> 00:20:27,090
I was so happy.

268
00:20:29,340 --> 00:20:32,630
In that moment, I thought,

269
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:38,410
"Ah, maybe he could be..."

270
00:20:42,970 --> 00:20:47,460
But maybe it's impossible
for someone like me.

271
00:20:56,570 --> 00:20:57,920
Mom?

272
00:21:03,870 --> 00:21:06,020
This is great, Koharu.

273
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,140
Keep going.

274
00:21:11,930 --> 00:21:13,670
You can do it, Koharu.

275
00:21:16,730 --> 00:21:18,400
Do your best.

276
00:21:19,905 --> 00:21:22,230
Why didn't you ride the commuter boat?

277
00:21:22,230 --> 00:21:24,420
I told you, it was the last one.

278
00:21:27,329 --> 00:21:30,450
I'll go buy some more. For the second half.

279
00:21:30,450 --> 00:21:32,280
We're still in the first half?

280
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,665
Should I come too?

281
00:21:33,665 --> 00:21:35,405
I'm good, I'm good.

282
00:21:37,420 --> 00:21:39,270
He's totally drunk.

283
00:21:50,070 --> 00:21:51,520
Phew.

284
00:22:04,950 --> 00:22:05,950
Hm?

285
00:22:06,970 --> 00:22:08,050
Well...

286
00:22:13,293 --> 00:22:14,763
How do I put this?

287
00:22:20,156 --> 00:22:21,316
Thanks.

288
00:22:22,210 --> 00:22:24,600
Huh? For what?

289
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,970
For getting me to support Koharu.

290
00:22:35,306 --> 00:22:37,346
Compared to before,

291
00:22:38,610 --> 00:22:41,280
when I wasn't doing anything,

292
00:22:42,945 --> 00:22:44,894
I feel a sense of purpose.

293
00:22:44,894 --> 00:22:47,224
What are you, a retired old man?

294
00:22:51,193 --> 00:22:55,163
Well, if you're having fun,
that's good, right?

295
00:22:58,140 --> 00:22:59,630
Yeah.

296
00:23:00,839 --> 00:23:02,909
Today was fun.

297
00:23:02,909 --> 00:23:04,349
Really.

298
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:07,860
Just fun?

299
00:23:09,790 --> 00:23:10,800
Hm?

300
00:23:12,809 --> 00:23:16,629
Kakeru, what do you think about Koharu?

301
00:23:18,046 --> 00:23:19,246
Huh?

302
00:23:21,540 --> 00:23:24,270
Do you like Koharu?

303
00:23:30,410 --> 00:23:33,780
Are you sure about just being good friends?

304
00:23:33,780 --> 00:23:36,770
I don't know what kind of person you like.

305
00:23:36,770 --> 00:23:38,820
But if you keep hiding those feelings,

306
00:23:38,820 --> 00:23:40,970
won't all the colors fade away again?

307
00:23:40,970 --> 00:23:43,960
I'm sorry. I'm late.

308
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:46,615
I thought I'd give Kakeru and Koharu
some alone time.

309
00:23:46,615 --> 00:23:48,050
I'm still worried.

310
00:23:48,050 --> 00:23:50,230
Don't tell me you...

311
00:23:50,230 --> 00:23:52,800
Taking the first step
is terrifying for everyone.

312
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:55,080
But without that step,

313
00:23:55,080 --> 00:23:56,955
your feelings will never get through to them.

314
00:23:56,955 --> 00:23:59,435
Can I ask you for something?
